around in my head that I'll write up at the first threat of a game,
although probably not for a long, dramatic campaign. I'd never
maintain the pace.

I have a thing for angsty fallen-knight types. Leon Ermenegilde
Bartelemy de Boniface was once the heir to a duchy, until the onset of
leprosy and his scheming brother combined to take away his birthright
and cast him into the waiting arms of the Ordo Vitualamen, sort of a
St. Lazarus type of thing for the diseased, bastard scions, and
outcasts. I write about this guy on occasion, and I'd love to play him
as a PC.

Remember all that Battle Nun stuff?  I've always wanted to play a
female paladin, cleric, or ascetic fighter based on the nun concept,
perhaps as a holy warrior, inquisitor or exorcist, depending on the
game.

There are more, but that's all I got right now.

